Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 350 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Drain and roughly chop @dill pickle{1}(sliced). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{2}. Dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}; chop into bite-size pieces.

Place @butter{4%tbsp} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{} and microwave until melted, ~{30-60%seconds}. Add @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, @smoky mustard{1%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}; whisk until well combined.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{}, @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Bake on top rack until browned and tender, ~{40-45%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, carefully separate top slider buns from bottom slider buns (keep top buns connected and bottom buns connected). Arrange @slider buns{12} in a single layer in a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} (two #baking dishes{} for 8 servings).

Evenly sprinkle half the @cheddar cheese{1%cup} over bottom buns. Top with @smoked deli ham{8%ounce} and chopped pickle. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and remaining cheddar. Top with top buns to form sliders.

Spoon sesame mustard butter over sliders (if butter mixture has separated, whisk before using). Cover #baking dish{} tightly with #foil{}. Bake on middle rack for ~{20%minutes}.

While sliders bake, in a large #bowl{}, combine @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @olive oil{3%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Whisk until combined.

Add lettuce and @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} to bowl with dressing. Toss to combine.

Once sliders have baked 20 minutes, carefully remove and discard foil from baking dish. Return sliders to middle rack and bake, uncovered, until top buns are lightly browned and cheese melts, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Serve ham and cheese sliders, potato wedges, and salad family style.